issues.title: I want to use other g++ in "make test"
issues.body:
I use CentOS5. I install new version g++ as g++44 to compile llvm.

Tests is succeed if i change the following part in Makefile.PL.

```
makemaker_args->{CC} = 'g++44';
makemaker_args->{LD} = 'g++44';
```

Can you change this part to select CC and LD by user?

issues.title: Escape sequence is output as it is
issues.body:
I compiled this code to `hello.ll` with Compiler::CodeGenerator::LLVM.

``` perl
#!/usr/bin/env perl

use strict;
use warnings;

print "Hello Perl on LLVM!\n";
```

But output of `$ lli hello.ll` is:

``` zsh
$ lli hello.ll
Hello Perl on LLVM!\n%
$
```

---

My written code is here: https://github.com/nyarla/perl-llvm-sample

Enviroments:
- OSX Mountain Lion 10.8.5
- LLVM is compiled with this command:
  - `$ brew install https://raw.github.com/rhysd/homebrew/13dbf9d3af83297eec66eeee8e579d82ab598da2/Library/Formula/llvm.rb --HEAD --with-clang --with-libcxx --disable-assertions`
- Compiler::(Lexer|Parser|CodeGenerator::LLVM) is installed from your git repository.

commit.message:
Add Some Features.
    1) support 32bit architecture
    2) support package system
    3) support use/use base
    4) support global variable
    5) add some test codes
support multiple accessor of hash reference
support (set/get) accessor for hash reference object
support multiple accessor of array reference
support (set/get) accessor for array reference object

add some features.
    1) support nanboxing
    2) support subroutine
    3) support multi assign value
    4) add optimization pass
    5) support tail call optimization
support simple access to function argument (no boundary check)
support increment operator and while statement
